The paper discusses the use of social network data to improve user experience in data-driven digital systems, which is a topic that falls under the field of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of psycholinguistics and artificial intelligence to better understand human behavior online, which suggests that it could also fall under the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of longitudinal datasets to predict system status based on personality traits and emotions, which could fall under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the challenges of sharing personal data, which could fall under the category of computers and society (cs.CY).
